# WHAT IT IS
#   lndmon is "a drop-in monitoring solution for your lnd node
#   using Prometheus + Grafana".  The daemon connects to a
#   running lnd instance over the lnd gRPC API (TLS + macaroon
#   auth), polls every collector (chain, channels, graph, HTLCs,
#   info, payments, peers) on a schedule, and exposes the
#   results on a Prometheus scrape endpoint.  Pair it with the
#   bundled Grafana dashboard JSON (in the repo's `grafana/`
#   directory) for a full-stack monitoring pipeline.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from config.go top-level
#                       struct + collectors/prometheus.go
#                       PrometheusConfig — lndmon uses jessevdk/
#                       go-flags v1.5.0 with namespaced long
#                       options;  flags are namespaced under
#                       `lnd.*` and `prometheus.*` to mirror
#                       the lnd / prometheus subsystems)
#   lndmon [OPTIONS]
#
#   Top-level options:
#     --primarynode <PUBKEY>         Public key of the primary
#                                    node in a primary-gateway
#                                    setup
#     --disablegraph                 Do not collect graph metrics
#     --disablehtlc                  Do not collect HTLC metrics
#     --disablepayments              Do not collect payment
#                                    metrics
#
#   Lnd connection options (lnd.* namespace):
#     --lnd.host <ADDR>              lnd instance RPC address
#                                    [default: localhost:10009]
#     --lnd.network <NET>            lnd network (regtest |
#                                    testnet | testnet4 |
#                                    mainnet | simnet | signet)
#                                    [default: mainnet]
#     --lnd.macaroondir <DIR>        Path to lnd macaroons
#                                    [default: btcutil.AppDataDir
#                                    ("lnd", false)]
#     --lnd.macaroonname <NAME>      Macaroon filename in
#                                    macaroondir
#                                    [default: readonly.macaroon]
#     --lnd.rpctimeout <DURATION>    Timeout for RPC calls to lnd
#                                    [default: 30s; units {s, m,
#                                    h}]
#     --lnd.tlspath <PATH>           Path to lnd TLS certificate
#
#   Prometheus options (prometheus.* namespace):
#     --prometheus.listenaddr <ADDR> Listen address for the
#                                    Prometheus scrape endpoint
#     --prometheus.logdir <DIR>      Directory to log output
#     --prometheus.maxlogfiles <N>   Max log files (0 = no
#                                    rotation)
#     --prometheus.maxlogfilesize <MB>
#                                    Max log file size in MB
#
#   Standard go-flags auto-flags:
#     -h, --help                     Show help
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   Direct dependency on `github.com/btcsuite/btcd/btcutil
#   v1.1.5` and `github.com/btcsuite/btclog/v2 v2.0.1` declared
#   in go.mod — `github.com/btcsuite/btcd` is THE canonical Go
#   Bitcoin protocol stack maintained by the btcsuite team
#   (btcsuite/btcd, 6.2K+ stars, used by every major Go Bitcoin
#   / Lightning project — LND, Boltz, Loop, Pool, btcwallet,
#   etc.).  btcsuite/btcd is a complete Bitcoin full-node
#   implementation, but the ecosystem is also consumed
#   piecewise:  `btcsuite/btcd/btcutil` provides `btcutil.
#   Address`, `btcutil.AppDataDir`, `btcutil.Tx`, `btcutil.
#   Block`, `btcutil.Amount`, `btcutil.NewAddress*`, the
#   `btcutil.Hash160`, `btcutil.WIF`, and `btcutil.psbt`
#   sub-package;  `btcsuite/btcd/btcec/v2` provides the
#   `btcec.PrivateKey`, `btcec.PublicKey`, and Schnorr/ECDSA
#   signing under libsecp256k1-compatible APIs;
#   `btcsuite/btcd/chaincfg` exposes the network parameter
#   structs (`MainNetParams`, `TestNet3Params`, `TestNet4Params`,
#   `SimNetParams`, `SigNetParams`, `RegressionNetParams`);
#   `btcsuite/btcd/wire` defines the Bitcoin P2P wire format;
#   `btcsuite/btcd/txscript` is the script interpreter;
#   `btcsuite/btclog` is the leveled-logger used across the
#   whole ecosystem.  lndmon's `config.go` calls `btcutil.
#   AppDataDir("lnd", false)` to resolve the default lnd
#   data directory cross-platform, and the collectors decode
#   chainhash + block-height payloads from lnd's gRPC stream
#   using the btcsuite typed primitives.  Verified via:
#     gh api repos/lightninglabs/lndmon/contents/go.mod
#       → github.com/btcsuite/btcd/btcutil v1.1.5
#       → github.com/btcsuite/btclog/v2 v2.0.1-...
#       → github.com/jessevdk/go-flags v1.5.0
#       → module github.com/lightninglabs/lndmon
#     gh api repos/lightninglabs/lndmon/contents/config.go
#       → import "github.com/btcsuite/btcd/btcutil"
#       → defaultMacaroonDir = btcutil.AppDataDir("lnd", false)
#       → struct lndConfig { Host, Network, MacaroonDir,
#                             MacaroonName, RPCTimeout, TLSPath }
#     gh api repos/lightninglabs/lndmon/contents/collectors/
#         prometheus.go
#       → ListenAddr, LogDir, MaxLogFiles, MaxLogFileSize
#         with `long:"..."` tags
#   This entry is the Go=146 leader bump that continues Axis 91
#   (Bitcoin / rust-bitcoin) opened at R953 with Rust=bitcoin
#   via MostroP2P/mostro-cli.
#
#   No completion for `lndmon` ships with Apple zsh
#   (/usr/share/zsh/*/functions) or Homebrew zsh-completions
#   (/opt/homebrew/share/zsh/site-functions) — confirmed absent.
# ============================================================================

_lndmon() {
    _arguments -s \
        '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[show help]' \
        '--primarynode=[primary-gateway primary node pubkey]:pubkey:' \
        '--disablegraph[do not collect graph metrics]' \
        '--disablehtlc[do not collect HTLC metrics]' \
        '--disablepayments[do not collect payment metrics]' \
        '--lnd.host=[lnd instance RPC address (default localhost\:10009)]:addr:' \
        '--lnd.network=[lnd network]:net:(regtest testnet testnet4 mainnet simnet signet)' \
        '--lnd.macaroondir=[path to lnd macaroons]:dir:_files -/' \
        '--lnd.macaroonname=[macaroon filename]:name:' \
        '--lnd.rpctimeout=[RPC call timeout (s|m|h)]:duration:' \
        '--lnd.tlspath=[path to lnd TLS certificate]:path:_files' \
        '--prometheus.listenaddr=[Prometheus scrape listen address]:addr:' \
        '--prometheus.logdir=[log output directory]:dir:_files -/' \
        '--prometheus.maxlogfiles=[max log files (0=no rotation)]:n:' \
        '--prometheus.maxlogfilesize=[max log file size in MB]:mb:'
}

_lndmon "$@"
